text:
Aroma: citrus, flour, lemon, hints of licorice, a bit of peach, great smell, but not very powerful ;
Appearance: very hazy pale deep yellow, light white non persistent foam ;
Taste: low bitterness, low to medium sweetness ;
Palate: medium to full body, low carbonation, a bit rough on the palate, abrupt finish.
To me, not worth all the fuss. The Stigbergets GBG is way better and cheaper, even though it is not even a DIPA. Ill compare it to the (un)human cannonball, because everyone seems to do so. Well, to me, the Cannonball variants are way more sophisticated and waaaaay better than this (still very good) beer.
For the record, I feel extremely lucky to have had the opportunity to taste both of these terribly rare brews.
